-- New York Knicks Give Head Coach Mike Woodson Multiyear Contract
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-05-25T22:04:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/new-york-knicks-give-head-coach-mike-woodson-multiyear-contract.html
The National Basketball Association’s
 New York Knicks  have given head coach Mike Woodson a multiyear
contract extension, the team announced today in an e-mailed
release.  Terms of the deal were not disclosed.  Woodson, who was promoted from assistant coach when Mike
D’Antoni resigned on March 14, led the Knicks to an 18-6
regular-season record as interim head coach. New York lost in
five games in the first round of the NBA playoffs.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  